1
00:00:01,368 --> 00:00:03,935
<i>Previously on</i> Young Sheldon...
Paige?

2
00:00:03,970 --> 00:00:05,837
I'm so happy to see you.

3
00:00:05,872 --> 00:00:07,205
Are you happy to see me?

4
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:09,207
Not immediately.

5
00:00:09,242 --> 00:00:11,410
I don't usually see young people
at my lectures.

6
00:00:11,445 --> 00:00:14,312
I enjoyed your paper on
accelerator mass spectrometry

7
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:15,680
and wanted to find out more.

8
00:00:15,715 --> 00:00:18,350
And you?
I read this magazine.

9
00:00:18,385 --> 00:00:20,685
Uh-huh.
It has puzzles, too.

10
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,587
Well, I think my parents
are getting a divorce.

11
00:00:22,622 --> 00:00:25,390
Why?
They fight all the time.

12
00:00:25,425 --> 00:00:28,360
I guess I'm lucky.
Why?

13
00:00:28,395 --> 00:00:31,397
I'm the glue that holds
our family together.

14
00:00:39,172 --> 00:00:41,907
What do you think of these?

15
00:00:41,942 --> 00:00:44,242
They're nice, but you're
already taller than John.

16
00:00:44,277 --> 00:00:45,710
Won't they make that worse?

17
00:00:45,745 --> 00:00:47,546
No, makes it better.

18
00:00:47,581 --> 00:00:49,281
He likes me to be dominating.

19
00:00:49,316 --> 00:00:51,083
I don't want to hear that.

20
00:00:51,118 --> 00:00:55,554
Sometimes he makes me wear these
when we're... messing around.

21
00:00:55,589 --> 00:00:57,989
I said I don't
want to hear it.

22
00:00:58,024 --> 00:01:00,092
I wanted to say it.

23
00:01:00,127 --> 00:01:03,462
All right, I don't have the
Sperry loafers in your size,

24
00:01:03,497 --> 00:01:05,697
but I do have the Hush Puppies.

25
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:08,200
I don't wear brown Hush
Puppies penny loafers,

26
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:10,469
I wear brown Sperry
penny loafers.

27
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:12,537
But they're exactly the same.
Well, do they come

28
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:14,372
in a box that says
Sperry penny loafers?

29
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,007
Because that one
says Hush Puppies.

30
00:01:16,042 --> 00:01:17,943
Just try 'em on, honey.

31
00:01:17,978 --> 00:01:20,812
What if I like them?
Well, then we'll get them.

32
00:01:20,847 --> 00:01:23,081
All right, let's go
over this again.

33
00:01:23,116 --> 00:01:25,417
I don't wear brown Hush
Puppies penny loafers,

34
00:01:25,452 --> 00:01:27,018
I wear brown Sperry...

35
00:01:27,053 --> 00:01:28,253
Would you give us a moment?

36
00:01:28,288 --> 00:01:29,988
Happily.

37
00:01:30,023 --> 00:01:32,157
When we get to
the Hello Kitty store today,

38
00:01:32,192 --> 00:01:34,259
remember I was the good child.

39
00:01:34,294 --> 00:01:35,894
Oh, hi, Mary.

40
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:37,762
Linda. So good to see you.

41
00:01:37,797 --> 00:01:40,165
Hi, Sheldon.
Hello, Paige.

42
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,833
Hi, Missy.
Hi!

43
00:01:41,868 --> 00:01:44,603
Look at these rain boots--
they have ducks on them.

44
00:01:44,638 --> 00:01:46,571
And the ducks
are wearing boots.

45
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:48,440
Those are so cute.

46
00:01:49,676 --> 00:01:51,910
Well, what a nice coincidence.
Yeah.

47
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:52,911
Good to see you.

48
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,045
Yeah. How are things?

49
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,180
Well, at the moment,

50
00:01:55,215 --> 00:01:56,648
trying to get shoes for Sheldon,

51
00:01:56,683 --> 00:02:00,051
but they only have these,
not the ones he likes.

52
00:02:00,086 --> 00:02:05,657
Ah. You know, I think that brand
is the same kind Einstein wore.

53
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:08,460
Well, I've never seen a picture
of his feet.

54
00:02:08,495 --> 00:02:11,029
And you're a grown-up,
so you wouldn't lie to me.

55
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:14,666
I guess I have no choice
but to believe you.

56
00:02:14,701 --> 00:02:16,368
All right, I'll try them.

57
00:02:16,403 --> 00:02:19,004
Great!

58
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:22,073
Hey, Mom, can Missy and I go
to the Hello Kitty store?

59
00:02:22,108 --> 00:02:24,609
Well, it's okay with me
if it's okay with Mary.

60
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:27,479
It's okay, but you better be
on your best behavior.

61
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:28,914
I will, I promise.

62
00:02:28,949 --> 00:02:29,948
Go ahead.

63
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:32,717
Boy, you steal
one pencil sharpener

64
00:02:32,752 --> 00:02:34,753
and you never hear
the end of it.

65
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:38,657
How do they feel?

66
00:02:38,692 --> 00:02:42,528
My brand loyalty is being
severely tested.

67
00:02:44,364 --> 00:02:47,265
<i> Nobody else
is stronger than I am </i>

68
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,935
<i> Yesterday I moved a mountain </i>

69
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:52,637
<i> I bet I could be your hero </i>

70
00:02:52,672 --> 00:02:54,906
<i> I am a mighty little man </i>

71
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:59,411
I am a mighty little man.

72
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:08,620
Did you guys know Paige
speaks three languages?

73
00:03:08,655 --> 00:03:11,389
Really?
That's impressive.

74
00:03:11,424 --> 00:03:13,525
You only speak one.

75
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,661
Two. I'm learning
conversational Klingon.

76
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:18,263
That's impressive, too.

77
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,534
Hey, Mom, can Paige
sleep over this weekend?

78
00:03:22,569 --> 00:03:24,803
I guess,
if her mother says okay.

79
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:27,005
Wait, where is she
going to sleep?

80
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,140
In your bed.
You can sleep on the couch.

81
00:03:29,175 --> 00:03:30,475
Absolutely not.

82
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:32,310
I've already changed
my brand of loafers,

83
00:03:32,345 --> 00:03:35,547
I am not changing
my sleeping quarters.

84
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:37,716
How about you stay at
Meemaw's? You like that.

85
00:03:37,751 --> 00:03:39,951
No, Meemaw has a date.

86
00:03:39,986 --> 00:03:40,752
So?

87
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:42,254
So if those shoes I just bought

88
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:43,688
do their job,

89
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:45,724
that will be a "no children
allowed" scenario.

90
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,961
Well, I'm sleeping in my bed,
and that's that.

91
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:52,297
Fine, Paige and I
can share my bed.

92
00:03:52,332 --> 00:03:53,832
You okay with that, Shelly?

93
00:03:53,867 --> 00:03:57,736
I trust you two will stay quiet
throughout the evening

94
00:03:57,771 --> 00:03:59,604
and go to sleep at
the appropriate time?

95
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:02,040
Absolutely.

96
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,843
All right, then.
I'm okay with it, Mom.

97
00:04:04,878 --> 00:04:08,847
How is he ever gonna
get through this world?

98
00:04:11,951 --> 00:04:13,952
Welcome, come on in.

99
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:15,820
Oh, thank you.

100
00:04:15,855 --> 00:04:18,423
You look nice. Going out
to dinner with your husband?

101
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,258
Ugh, no. Girlfriends.

102
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:21,493
Hi, Sheldon.

103
00:04:21,528 --> 00:04:22,994
Hello.

104
00:04:23,029 --> 00:04:24,062
What are you doing?

105
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,097
Chemistry homework
for extra credit.

106
00:04:26,132 --> 00:04:27,966
Cute, I did that last year.

107
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:29,768
Paige!

108
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:31,503
Missy!

109
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:33,705
Aw, they're so sweet.

110
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:37,309
Yeah, life'll suck that
right out of them soon enough.

111
00:04:37,344 --> 00:04:38,743
Well, bye.
Bye.

112
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:42,080
You got to meet my dolls--
I told them all about you!

113
00:04:44,818 --> 00:04:48,153
"Cute, I did that last year."

114
00:04:48,188 --> 00:04:50,522
Thank you for agreeing
to the early-bird dinner.

115
00:04:50,557 --> 00:04:54,626
When I eat too late,
the food just sits right here.

116
00:04:54,661 --> 00:04:57,028
Yeah, gettin' old
is no party.

117
00:04:57,063 --> 00:05:00,198
Oh, I've had this problem
since I was ten.

118
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:05,170
When I was in grade school,
my nickname was Old Burpy.

119
00:05:05,205 --> 00:05:08,106
Well, I will not be
calling you that.

120
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,374
You can if you'd like.

121
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:10,775
I'm good.

122
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:13,545
So, I have a little surprise
for you.

123
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,680
Oh, I love surprises.
Whatcha got?

124
00:05:15,715 --> 00:05:17,549
I'm going to learn to drive.

125
00:05:17,584 --> 00:05:19,384
Really?

126
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:20,752
Yes.

127
00:05:20,787 --> 00:05:24,022
While I love having you be
the dominant personality

128
00:05:24,057 --> 00:05:27,525
behind closed doors,
I think out in public

129
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,494
I ought to take on
more of a macho role.

130
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:33,798
Well, you're macho enough
for me, John,

131
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:37,268
but I would enjoy not having
to drive us all the time.

132
00:05:37,303 --> 00:05:38,470
Then it's settled.

133
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:40,205
Well, when do you start?

134
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,806
As soon as you teach me.

135
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:45,810
Me? Do you really think
that's a good idea?

136
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:49,280
It's perfect.
I teach you about science

137
00:05:49,315 --> 00:05:50,815
so you can impress
your grandson,

138
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:54,853
and you teach me to drive
so I can impress you.

139
00:05:54,888 --> 00:05:59,357
Okay, but if we do this,
I'm in charge.

140
00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:04,329
You have to do what I say when
and how I tell you to do it.

141
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:08,433
Hubba-hubba, it's like
we're back in the bedroom.

142
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:13,571
Did you know that tea was
discovered by accident?

143
00:06:13,606 --> 00:06:16,107
I didn't, but I don't know
lots of stuff.

144
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:18,810
The Emperor Shennong of China
was boiling water in his garden

145
00:06:18,845 --> 00:06:21,446
and a leaf from a tea tree
fell into his pot.

146
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:23,715
Tea comes from trees?

147
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,984
Where'd you think
it comes from?

148
00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:29,020
The supermarket.

149
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:32,257
What, the girls leave you out
of their little picnic?

150
00:06:32,292 --> 00:06:33,658
Oh, they invited him.

151
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:35,026
Well, then why ain't you
out there?

152
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:38,329
Eat outdoors? Do I look
like a hippie to you?

153
00:06:38,364 --> 00:06:39,998
I thought Paige
was your friend.

154
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:41,966
She's more of a colleague.

155
00:06:42,001 --> 00:06:42,801
Oh.

156
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:44,135
Although for reasons unknown,

157
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,337
she's currently behaving
like a ten-year-old.

158
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:48,773
Maybe that's because she
is a ten-year-old.

159
00:06:48,808 --> 00:06:50,208
Still no excuse.

160
00:06:52,111 --> 00:06:54,012
All right, I'm just gonna
come out and ask it:

161
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:56,648
what the heck
is a colleague?

162
00:07:03,723 --> 00:07:04,989
Okay, pick a number.

163
00:07:05,024 --> 00:07:05,890
Three.

164
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:07,759
One, two, three.

165
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:09,360
Now pick a color.

166
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:10,628
Pink, duh.

167
00:07:10,663 --> 00:07:15,433
The name of
your future pony is...

168
00:07:15,468 --> 00:07:17,368
Sparkle Sunshine.

169
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:19,404
I would totally name it that!

170
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,373
Sheldon, do you want to
have your fortune read?

171
00:07:22,408 --> 00:07:24,042
Absolutely not.

172
00:07:24,077 --> 00:07:27,278
And I cannot believe a person
as smart as you is doing it.

173
00:07:27,313 --> 00:07:29,180
Why? It's fun.

174
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:32,684
He doesn't know how to have fun;
he's an old man.

175
00:07:32,719 --> 00:07:34,052
I'm not an old man.

176
00:07:34,087 --> 00:07:36,387
Oh, yeah?
What's your favorite color?

177
00:07:36,422 --> 00:07:37,655
Khaki.

178
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:39,958
Old man.

179
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,634
I'm trying to sleep.

180
00:07:49,669 --> 00:07:51,636
Come inside and play with us.

181
00:07:51,671 --> 00:07:52,837
Don't invite him.

182
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:54,172
This is a girls' fort,

183
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:55,607
not an old man fort.

184
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:57,809
I'm not an old man.

185
00:07:57,844 --> 00:07:59,077
Then come inside.

186
00:07:59,112 --> 00:08:01,279
Are you crazy? It's bedtime.

187
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,982
Old man.

188
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:05,917
(Paige and Missy laughing)

189
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:13,074
