190
00:08:23,269 --> 00:08:25,136
What are you doing?

191
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,539
We're tying
Georgie's ankles together.

192
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:30,441
So when he gets
out of bed he falls down.

193
00:08:30,476 --> 00:08:31,843
But he could get hurt.

194
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:33,578
If we're lucky.

195
00:08:33,613 --> 00:08:36,014
Well, I will not be
a party to this.

196
00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:37,582
Old man.

197
00:08:41,287 --> 00:08:44,956
That's when
the bloodthirsty Goatman--

198
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:47,125
part goat, part man--

199
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:51,529
crept up on the
sleeping children...
No.

200
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:56,467
...and sank his sharp little
teeth into their necks...
No.

201
00:08:56,502 --> 00:08:58,670
...and drank their blood!

202
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:00,338
No.

203
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:01,839
Problem?

204
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:04,075
Several. First of all,
goats are herbivores.

205
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,277
They don't eat meat,
let alone drink blood.

206
00:09:06,312 --> 00:09:08,413
Maybe the half man part
drinks blood.

207
00:09:08,448 --> 00:09:11,783
Don't even get me started
on the "half man" stuff.

208
00:09:11,818 --> 00:09:15,186
Sheldon, it's just
a fun scary story.

209
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,255
It's nonsense is what it is.

210
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:18,489
Old man.

211
00:09:18,524 --> 00:09:20,291
I'm not an old man, I'm ten.

212
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:21,693
More like 110.

213
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:25,163
You know, I read that adults
who had a stunted childhood

214
00:09:25,198 --> 00:09:27,865
often become social misfits
and weirdos.

215
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,500
You didn't read that,
you're making it up

216
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:31,069
like your goat story.

217
00:09:31,104 --> 00:09:35,506
<i>Psychology Magazine,</i>
February issue, 1988.

218
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:36,808
Well, um...

219
00:09:36,843 --> 00:09:39,210
That doesn't make it true.

220
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,245
Guess you'll find out
when you're an adult.

221
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,148
I guess I will.

222
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,219
<i> Well, we know</i>
<i>how this story ends.</i>

223
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:50,321
<i>I grew up to become</i>
<i>a well-adjusted</i>

224
00:09:50,356 --> 00:09:52,390
<i>and charming fellow.</i>
<i>But at that moment in time,</i>

225
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,625
<i>she had me worried.</i>

226
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:58,296
<i> Hey, Georgie, breakfast.</i>
<i>Mom made Eggos.</i>

227
00:09:58,331 --> 00:10:00,331
<i>Eggos, sweet.</i>

228
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:02,700
<i>Ow! Dang it!</i>

229
00:10:11,678 --> 00:10:12,644
Oh, dear.

230
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:13,678
What?

231
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:15,246
Paige was right.

232
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:17,248
"There's ample evidence
to indicate

233
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:20,551
"that a stunted childhood
can cause one to be maladjusted

234
00:10:20,586 --> 00:10:21,686
as an adult."

235
00:10:21,721 --> 00:10:22,954
Then I'm screwed.

236
00:10:22,989 --> 00:10:24,489
What do you mean?

237
00:10:24,524 --> 00:10:27,191
When I'm not in school,
I'm doing homework.

238
00:10:27,226 --> 00:10:29,961
When I'm not doing homework,
I'm practicing my cello.

239
00:10:29,996 --> 00:10:31,396
And when I'm not doing that,

240
00:10:31,431 --> 00:10:33,197
I'm working
in my parents' store.

241
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:35,800
That must be why we're friends.

242
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:37,035
We're both stunted.

243
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:38,403
Sounds right.

244
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:41,572
Well, I for one
plan to do something about it.

245
00:10:41,607 --> 00:10:43,241
Like what?

246
00:10:43,276 --> 00:10:46,244
I'm going to goof off,
engage in horseplay,

247
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,613
and if time permits,
be quite immature.

248
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,981
If time permits?

249
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:52,116
I have homework, too.

250
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:54,318
Would you like to join me
in my shenanigans?

251
00:10:54,353 --> 00:10:55,653
No, thanks.

252
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:59,123
Aren't you concerned about
being a maladjusted adult?

253
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,726
Nah. I'll just marry
an American woman

254
00:11:01,761 --> 00:11:04,295
and hope she can fix me.

